            {
              "id": "datadog/python-insecurecookie",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Potential insecure cookie configuration"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "In Python, Insecure Cookie (CWE-614) occurs when cookies storing sensitive input are set without\nsecurity attributes (secure, httponly, samesite).\n\nFor example (vulnerable):\n```python\nresponse.set_cookie(\"session_id\", session_id)  # Missing security attributes\n```\n\n## How to remediate:\n- Set secure=True for HTTPS-only transmission.\n- Set httponly=True to prevent JavaScript access.\n- Set samesite=\"Strict\" or \"Lax\" for CSRF protection."
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": [
                  "DATADOG_RULE_TYPE:datadog-ai-static-analyzer",
                  "CWE:614",
